reviewText: i was a little confused by the strange range of reviews.  they were heavy enough on the negative side that i almost didn't watch.  glad i did.  it really is pretty good.  some of the acting could be better, and about ten minutes of it was wasted on unnecessary filler.  still, i liked it.  one of these days i might watch it again.one thing i really love is the song played at the end of the credits, "it's only you" by felix linden.  liked it so much, i coughed up a whole $.99 for it.  now that's a song worth listening to.
summary: not as bad as they say
Title: HE'S ON MY MIND

reviewText: Thank God for Amazon Prime because I would have been highly upset to have paid to rent this "movie."  I was trying to make it to the end but just couldn't!  Watching someone barf right into someone lap while on a ferris wheel is not my cup of tea!  This film definitely proves that you don't have to go to film school to write a script.  Before I die, I guess I'll take a stab at it and I can bet it'll be 10 times better than this crap!
summary: The Worst I've seen in a long time!

reviewText: Ok the acting was horrible, it was definitely an amateur work but I guess exposure for the lead actress Sherial McKinney et al. She looks so much like a younger Halle Berry, without trying but also seemed to try to act like her as well. the story reminded me of a cross between Boomerang with the Eddie cheating on her and coming back and it reminds me about a reverse role of the movie where the guy can read women's thoughts. It doesn't explain how that happened for her to hear men's thoughts other than she woke up in the library and read a bunch of books. It was predictable in that you knew how the movie ended.  I can't believe I watched this  but I skipped through this after the first five minutes. I surfed the net most of the time.
summary: Glad I didn't pay to see it
Title: HE'S ON MY MIND
